name: Attack Scenario
description: Attack Scenario is Recordtype for Scenario Objecttype. An Attack Scenario is root element of Attack Tree

name: Attack:Vector
description: An Attack Vector is Recordtype for Objecttype Pathway.  An Attack Vector is a node element of Attack Tree

name: Target:Facilities
description: Terminals, Stations, Hubs, Fuel Depots, Storate Facilities, Headquarters Buildings, and Operations, Communications, & Dispatch Centers. Facilities may be targets or the path to harm conveyances or other sector infrastructure.

name: Target:Conveyances
description: Planes, Trains, Boats, & Automotive Vehicles. Conveyances may be targets or weapons depending on size, speed capability, or what they are carrying.

name: Target:Pathway (Route)
description: Air, Ground, Underground, and Water mediums for travel. Pathways may be corrupted to reroute, damage, disable or delay conveyances.

name: Target:Intermediaries
description: Brokers, agents, consolidators, vendors and contractors who facilitate travel of passengers and cargo. Intermediaries provide support function and present insider threat opportunities.

name: Target:Security Control Points
description: Locations not part of the transportation system, but are either at risk from transportation or pose a risk to transportation. For exampe: an identified MANPADS launch site or the nexus between a TIH rail route and a stadium.

name: Weapon:Chemical Agent
description: Release of weaponized or industrial chemicals in populated areas.  Releaes could be from a transportation medium such a a rail car or a truck or an attack on a transportation passenger facility such as a train station,cruise terminal or airport.

name: Weapon:Cyber Attack (Hack)
description: Attacks on information technology systems to disrupt transportation operations, create a diversion for another attack, remotely comandier traffic control or routing systems or information theft to inform a later attack.

name: Weapon:Explosives (Bombs)
description: Explosive devices may be implanted in automotive vehicles car bombs, planted on the roadside to detonate near traffic, or strapped to the bodies of individuals for suicide attacks.

name: Weapon:Hostage Taking
description: Terrorist operation used to abduct individuals (kidnap), hold groups of individuals to occupy a space or trade for political concesions, or hijack a conveyance for the pruposes of a kinetic attack.

name: Weapon: Kinetic  Weapon
description: The use of a transportation vehicle to ram into a target.  If the vehicle has enough flammable liquid in a fuel of cargo tank the collision can have an incendiary or or explosive effect in addition to the damage caused by the initial collision.

name: Weapon:Stand-Off Weapon
description: Remote attacks using long range weapons such as sniper rifles, rocket launchers or small artillery.

name: Weapon:Radiological Materials
description: Use of radiological materials to cause mass casualties and/or environmental contamination. Casualties may result from massive explosion (nuclear device) or widespread illness resulting from radiation poisoning.

name: Weapon:Sabatoge
description: Actively damaging components to cause failure of transportation system - particularly conveyances.

name: Counter Measure:Technology
description: Counter Measure:Technology are applicable to Attack Methods

name: Counter Measure:Personnel
description: Counter Measure:Personnel are applicable to Attack Methods

name: Counter Measure:Process
description: Counter Measure:Process are applicable to Attack Methods

name: Attack:Method
description: An Attack Method  is Recordtype for Objecttype Pathway.  An Attack Method is sub-node element of an Attack Vector

name: Attack:Goal
description: An Attack:Goal  is Recordtype for Objecttype Pathway.  An Attack Goal  is the  root element of Attack Tree

name: Counter Measure:Infrastructure
description: Counter Measure:Infrastructure  are applicable to Attack Methods

name: Counter Measure:Policy
description: Counter Measure:Policy are applicable to Attack Methods
